00:55:11,440 --> 00:55:15,500
You know, people, you can imagine the person after shedding the body, they say,

719
00:55:16,000 --> 00:55:19,900
"Oh God, I spent all my life caring for this thing, and it's rotting now."

720
00:55:24,260 --> 00:55:31,619
You think, "I went to school, took tests, got a good degree, had a good job..."

721
00:55:33,460 --> 00:55:37,420
I spent my life caring for this thing; what did I do for my self?

722
00:55:38,300 --> 00:55:46,179
Now, what you do for your self are the spiritual tools: the prayers, the fasting, the charity (the Zakat), the righteous works,

723
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:50,519
worshiping God, remembering God, because your soul is what profits from that.

724
00:55:56,039 --> 00:55:59,699
But if you are ill or suffering some head injury, then you may cut your hair,

725
00:55:59,699 --> 00:6:04,039
and expiate by fasting, or giving a charity, or some other form of worship.

726
00:56:04,820 --> 00:56:09,800
For one who enjoys the time of peace between Umrah and Hajj,

727
00:56:09,920 --> 00:56:11,860
then expiate by offering a sacrifice.

728
00:56:14,800 --> 00:56:22,460
When we were making Hajj, my father wanted to break the Ihram between Umrah and Hajj.

729
00:56:22,460 --> 00:56:29,900
Because it was many days; we were there from the first day of the month until the 8th.

730
00:56:31,079 --> 00:56:38,539
And then the official day of Hajj is the 8th day. Everybody must be in Mina on the 8th day.

731
00:56:41,199 --> 00:56:48,619
This is the day of Hajj, the 8th. On the 9th day, everybody must be on Mount Arafat.

732
00:56:48,619 --> 00:57:00,940
So we went on the first, we went for Umrah on the first. Now we had eight days, and my father wanted to relax, spend these waiting days, whatever he wanted to do, so he had to satisfy his needs.

733
00:57:04,260 --> 00:57:12,599
And this was his burden. I told him not to break the Ihram. So I told him to be mindful of his oath.

734
00:57:14,840 --> 00:57:24,440
Yes. When you go for Hajj, the requirements are that you go to Arafat and perform the rites at the Ka'bah.

735
00:57:25,440 --> 00:57:32,619
Well, most of the practices came to us, like Salat, through Abraham, but actually most of them have been mentioned here.

736
00:57:33,820 --> 00:57:40,679
No, the Sha'a'er (rites) are mentioned here. The running between Safa and Marwah is mentioned here.

737
00:57:42,019 --> 00:57:47,340
And Arafat is also mentioned. Arafat is mentioned in verse 198.

738
00:57:48,300 --> 00:57:48,860
198?

739
00:57:49,219 --> 00:57:51,360
198.

740
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:52,940
In that verse it's mentioned.

741
00:57:53,199 --> 00:57:53,760
198.

742
00:57:54,800 --> 00:57:59,699
Yeah, that's right. Arafat is mentioned. So Arafat is mentioned in verse 198.

743
00:58:00,819 --> 00:58:03,599
So, almost everything in Hajj is mentioned in the Quran.

744
00:58:05,619 --> 00:58:09,980
Now, when you go around the Ka'bah seven times,

745
00:58:11,360 --> 00:58:13,460
it will feel like it's being worshipped.

746
00:58:16,099 --> 00:58:17,639
So you're going around the building,

747
00:58:20,179 --> 00:58:23,000
and people will ask you, "Are you worshipping this thing?"

748
00:58:23,340 --> 00:58:26,500
And that's why the language of the Quran is very important here in Hajj.

749
00:58:26,500 --> 00:58:29,780
But with God's help, it is certainly all right to go around the Ka'bah.

750
00:58:29,860 --> 00:58:30,539
This is how it is.

751
00:58:30,820 --> 00:58:33,260
You are not committing a sin by circling the Ka'bah.

752
00:58:33,460 --> 00:58:34,539
This is how it is.

753
00:58:34,840 --> 00:58:37,119
Another example for you is what was there.

754
00:58:37,139 --> 00:58:37,719
What did He say?

755
00:58:38,679 --> 00:58:42,300
The language of Quran is very, it's like God said,

756
00:58:42,539 --> 00:58:44,920
"Prostrate before Adam."

757
00:58:45,099 --> 00:58:47,360
Are they worshipping Adam?

758
00:58:48,059 --> 00:58:48,699
Or what?

759
00:58:48,760 --> 00:58:52,719
So, it is by permission from God that we do this.

760
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:54,659
We do this because we are obedient to God.

761
00:58:55,299 --> 00:59:00,000
And the angels prostrated before Adam, not because they worshipped Adam, but in obedience to God.

762
00:59:02,159 --> 00:59:06,119
And this prostration to the ground is a very, very simple and an insignificant act.

763
00:59:08,619 --> 00:59:13,500
So the conclusion is that this act of following the command is all right.

764
00:59:14,259 --> 00:59:15,059
All right.

765
00:59:16,460 --> 00:59:17,679
The second question.

766
00:59:17,780 --> 00:59:19,659
You are not committing a sin by

767
00:59:20,320 --> 00:59:21,000
prostrating

768
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:23,280
on the

769
00:59:23,280 --> 00:59:24,019
ground to do it.

770
00:59:26,760 --> 00:59:27,659
No, you see,

771
00:59:27,739 --> 00:59:29,320
you commemorate God during these days.

772
00:59:29,320 --> 00:59:30,000
It is like that.

773
00:59:31,440 --> 00:59:32,420
You can leave

774
00:59:33,199 --> 00:59:34,800
in two days, and you commit

775
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:37,039
no error. And if you delay,

776
00:59:37,039 --> 00:59:37,619
you commit no error.
